On Take Your Child to Work Day millions of children cut school to hang out at their parents’ offices. In offices around the country, we shared Soaringwords community service projects with employees' children at New York Life Insurance Company, Cisco,  Presidio and The Boston Consulting Group (BCG). The worst decision my Dad ever made was to purchase Long Term Care Insurance from New York Life!! 

My Dad bought a policy for my Mom in 1994. He wanted to ensure she would get the care she needed if he died before she did. He did. He paid 937.00 a year for 21 years, a total of over 19,000 dollars. 

New York Life is keeping the premium payment for the year(s) 2015 and 2016. She used the policy and they paid claims starting in April of 2015! Her claim was activated March of 2015.

She is in memory care now and the policy pays 60 dollars per day. The problem is that there is a waiting period of 180 days. 

I don't understand how they can keep premium payments and pay out a claim at the same time! 

I have had numerous conversations with customer service, claims, and have even spoken with someone who is supposed to be a Vice President over claims and have gotten nothing but the run-around.

YOU WOULD BE MUCH BETTER OFF TO PUT AWAY MONEY FOR ANY LONG TERM CARE NEEDED THAN TO PURCHASE THIS RIP-OFF POLICY THAT MAY NEVER PAY A CLAIM BECAUSE THE AVERAGE LIFE EXPECTANCY FOR AN ELDERLY PERSON ADMITTED TO A NURSING HOME IS FIVE MONTHS AND THE POLICY WAIT PERIOD IS SIX MONTHS!!

Buyer beware!

Learn from my family's costly mistake. Don't buy a Long Term Care Policy from New York Life!!
New York Life Insurance Company
